# ☁️ Cloud Backup Workflow -- Full Documentation

This document explains the complete **Google Auth + Google Drive +
CloudBackupService** workflow for your Flutter app.\
It includes **Mermaid diagrams** for quick visual understanding.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

## 1️⃣ High-Level Flowchart

``` mermaid
flowchart TD
    A[App Startup] --> B[DriveAuthService.init()]
    B -->|Silent sign-in success| C[AuthState = SignedIn]
    B -->|Silent sign-in fail| D[AuthState = SignedOut]

    C --> E[User taps "Backup Now"]
    D --> E

    E --> F[CloudBackupService.backupEncryptedZip()]
    F -->|interactive:true| G[DriveAuthService.getAuthHeaders()]
    F -->|interactive:false| H[DriveAuthService.getAuthHeaders()]

    G -->|OK| I[GoogleDriveService._getDriveApi()]
    H -->|Silent fail| J[Throw silentSignInRequired]

    I --> K[Upload ZIP to Drive]
    K --> L[BackupResult.success()]
    J --> M[Log + UI Badge: "Sign-in required"]
    L --> N[UI shows ✅ Backup Successful]
```

------------------------------------------------------------------------

## 2️⃣ Manual Backup Sequence

``` mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant UI
    participant CloudBackup as CloudBackupService
    participant DriveAuth as DriveAuthService
    participant DriveSvc as GoogleDriveService
    participant GoogleAPI as Google Drive API

    UI->>CloudBackup: backupEncryptedZip(zip, interactive:true)
    CloudBackup->>DriveSvc: uploadToAppData(zip, interactive:true)
    DriveSvc->>DriveAuth: getAuthHeaders(interactive:true)
    alt SignedOut
        DriveAuth->>User: Show Google Sign-In UI
        User-->>DriveAuth: Approves sign-in
    end
    DriveAuth-->>DriveSvc: Fresh Headers
    DriveSvc->>GoogleAPI: Create DriveApi + upload file
    GoogleAPI-->>DriveSvc: File(id, size)
    DriveSvc-->>CloudBackup: Success(fileId)
    CloudBackup-->>UI: Show success message + update history
```

------------------------------------------------------------------------

## 3️⃣ Auto-Backup (Non-Interactive)

``` mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant Scheduler
    participant CloudBackup as CloudBackupService
    participant DriveAuth as DriveAuthService
    participant DriveSvc as GoogleDriveService

    Scheduler->>CloudBackup: backupEncryptedZip(zip, interactive:false)
    CloudBackup->>DriveSvc: uploadToAppData(zip, interactive:false)
    DriveSvc->>DriveAuth: getAuthHeaders(interactive:false)
    alt No session
        DriveAuth-->>DriveSvc: throw silentSignInRequired
        DriveSvc-->>CloudBackup: Exception
        CloudBackup-->>Scheduler: Mark as failed (no popup)
    else Session valid
        DriveAuth-->>DriveSvc: Fresh headers
        DriveSvc->>Google API: Upload file
        Google API-->>DriveSvc: OK
        DriveSvc-->>CloudBackup: Success
    end
```

------------------------------------------------------------------------

## 4️⃣ Account Switch Handling

``` mermaid
flowchart LR
    A[GoogleSignIn account changed] --> B[DriveAuthService broadcasts new AuthState]
    B --> C[GoogleDriveService.dispose()]
    C --> D[Clear cached DriveApi & folderId]
    D --> E[Next backup/restore builds new client with fresh headers]
```

------------------------------------------------------------------------

## 🧠 Notes & Recommendations

-   **Silent sign-in first**: avoid annoying users with UI prompts
    unless needed.
-   **Fresh headers per call**: prevents expired token errors.
-   **Auto-backup** should never show popups; just mark as failed and
    surface a gentle badge or toast.
-   **Dispose DriveApi on account switch** to avoid stale sessions.
-   **Test**: manual flow, auto-flow, account switch, and 404 recovery.

